name: Bill Walton
summary: NBA legend and Hall of Famer Bill Walton has passed away at the age of 71 after a prolonged battle with cancer. Walton, who played center for the Portland Trail Blazers, Boston Celtics, and San Diego Clippers, led the Trail Blazers to their first NBA championship in 1977. Walton was also a three-time NBA All-Star and two-time NBA Defensive Player of the Year. After retiring from playing, Walton became a successful broadcaster, covering NBA games for ESPN and the Pac-12 Network. Walton's legacy extends beyond his accomplishments on the court, as he was known for his outspoken personality and advocacy for social justice. His death has been met with an outpouring of grief from the basketball community and beyond.

summary: Western Bulldogs forward Rory Lobb has reportedly decided to seek a trade at the end of the season, potentially making him the first player to move clubs in the upcoming AFL trade period. The decision has sparked investor interest, with the company's shares rising on the ASX. However, some investors are questioning the compensation of Lendlease's CEO in light of the firm's recent financial performance, including a A$1.48 billion write-down on overseas developments. The company's strategic revamp is set to be discussed at a shareholder meeting on Monday. Despite the offshore exit, Lendlease remains optimistic about its domestic prospects, citing favorable market conditions and a strong pipeline of local projects.
